org.xmlrobot.name: parent
org.xmlrobot.key: parent project is a structured Maven Parent Project, a frequently XML programming order in Maven builds. This implementation centralizes configuration, dependencies, and properties that are inherited across complex POM sub- projects (frequently referred to as "child projects" or "modules"). The parent project contains a complex pom.xml file that sets settings, dependency ordering, plugins, and other configurations that will be inherited by all child projects. It sets project-inherited properties like Java version, dependency versions, or custom variables to main- tain order. Instead of duplicating configurations across multiple projects, these are maintained centrally in the parent POM.
